ğŸ”¥ Real Spring Boot Usage (Like Your Project)

List<UserDTO> dtos = users.stream()
    .filter(user -> user.isActive())        // Predicate
    .map(userMapper::toDto)                 // Function
    .peek(log::info)                        // Consumer
    .toList();

Functional interfaces enable lambda expressions by enforcing a single abstract method. Java provides built-in functional interfaces like Predicate, Function, Consumer, and Supplier to support functional-style programming

â€œJava is primarily an object-oriented language, but since Java 8 it also supports functional-style programming using lambdas, streams, and immutable data processing. In real projects, we use a hybrid approachâ€”OOP for structure and functional style for data processing.â€


